<paragraph id="8BEF3692000E254FAC961C37FB6AE6D8" blockId="2.[151,1437,1354,1669]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">
<emphasis id="B924EA80000E254FAC961C37FE5CE610" box="[199,400,1354,1380]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Female with seventh sternite basally transversely rectangular. Female pygofer slightly incurved and ovipositor of the female very long. First valvula of ovipositor narrowly blade-like with sculpture strigate. Second valvula narrow with a somewhat elongate rounded lobe basally, without dorsal teeth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6519000E254FAC961CCBFED8E56C" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BEF3692000E254FAC961CCBFED8E56C" blockId="2.[151,1437,1354,1669]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">
<emphasis id="B924EA80000E254FAC961CCBFEF7E6A4" bold="true" box="[199,315,1462,1488]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new genus resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D11000E254FAE2D1CCBFC7BE6A4" authority="Anufriev, 1969" authorityName="Anufriev" authorityYear="1969" box="[636,951,1462,1488]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bambusana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EA80000E254FAE2D1CCBFCCCE6A4" box="[636,768,1462,1488]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Bambusana</emphasis>
Anufriev, 
<quantity id="4CA89B77000E254FAF2E1CCBFC7BE6A4" box="[895,951,1462,1488]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.00126" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" unit="in" value="1969.0">1969</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in general appearance, but can be distinguished by the aedeagus with preatrium bearing pair of processes and a pair of phragma lobes with distinct short, stout setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6519000E254FAC961F5FFB4CE514" pageId="2" pageNumber="247" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BEF3692000E254FAC961F5FFB4CE514" blockId="2.[151,1437,1354,1669]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">
<emphasis id="B924EA80000E254FAC961F5FFE82E548" bold="true" box="[199,334,1570,1596]" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name is derived from the Latin words “ 
<emphasis id="B924EA80000E254FAFC31F5FFC04E548" box="[914,968,1570,1596]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">fusc-</emphasis>
” and “ 
<emphasis id="B924EA80000E254FA8471F5FFBA4E548" box="[1046,1128,1570,1596]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="247">macula</emphasis>
”, referring to the pronotum with two small symmetrical black spots and forewing with a large number of black spots.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
